DOCUMENT PRIVACY/SECURITY INVESTIGATION LOG
==========================================
Date: 2025-01-19
Issue: Documents from one chat are being used to answer questions in other chats

FINDINGS:
--------

1. CRITICAL BUG in /api/chat/simple endpoint (app.py, lines 424-433):
   - First searches for documents WITH session filter
   - If no results found, it FALLS BACK to searching WITHOUT session filter
   - This means documents from OTHER sessions can be accessed
   - This is a severe privacy/security vulnerability

2. CRITICAL BUG in _handle_documents_query function (app.py, lines 1118-1138):
   - Searches across ALL Pinecone indices
   - NO filtering by user_id or session_id
   - Any user can potentially access any document in the system
   - This is an even more severe security vulnerability

3. Document processor issues:
   - enhanced_document_processor.py properly stores session_id in metadata (line 223)
   - But the search implementation doesn't always use proper filtering

ROOT CAUSES:
-----------
1. Fallback logic in chat/simple endpoint that removes session filtering
2. No user/session filtering in the documents tool query handler
3. Inconsistent UUID format handling (with/without dashes)

FIXES NEEDED:
------------
1. Remove the fallback search without session filter in chat/simple endpoint
2. Add proper user/session filtering to _handle_documents_query
3. Ensure consistent UUID format handling throughout the system
4. Add validation to ensure users can only access their own documents

SEVERITY: CRITICAL
This allows users to access documents from other users' sessions, which is a severe privacy violation.